Figure 13 shows the relationship between stiffness (left panel)/strength (right panel) and the time graphene was exposed to plasma. The Raman curves are also presented to help correlate the exposure time to the defective state of the structure.

The importance of these results is that they allow probing the strength and stiffness of a batch of graphene which is to be used as reinforcing element in a nanocomposite by a simple Raman probing, i.e. in a much simpler way (which is also amenable to automation) than testing individual sheets.

